The banana🍌
The rise of the banana
Chapter 1
One day, there was a banana, on the floor and very much alone. First, the banana wondered
if there was more in life than just being a banana so the banana rolled around across the city,
through the roads, and over bridges. As the banana rolled he found many houses, buildings,
trees, and signs.
Second, after a very long time, the banana decided to try to find another banana. Days and
nights accumulated over a duration of time, days became weeks, weeks became months, and
months became years and over that span of time, he found nothing about other bananas.
Third, but after that span of time, he thought in his mind: “Why don’t I check inside the
buildings?”.He went inside a building with a sign that said “Shop” and saw a few dozen bananas
and he was shocked 🍌. If that wasn’t enough he then found a carving on the wall that said, “For
sale”.
Fourth, by now he was flabbergasted, as he tried saying stop he realized that since he was a
banana, he couldn't use human communication so he found that the object retaining up the
bananas was supported by a “twisty stick” that you know today as screws. He tried dislodging
the screw but he could not generate enough momentum so he instead attempted to twist it with
an edge that acted like a screwdriver to unscrew the screw and let numerous dozens of
bananas free.
Fifth, he was happy that he let go of some bananas out of the store and into the wild. But it was
not enough for him, he told the plan to his banana buds to launch an attack on stores, break the
banana aisle, and free hundreds to thousands to maybe even hundreds of thousands into the
wild, and his plan was successful.
Sixth, he was a banana hero… But he still wasn’t satisfied with his results as this was only one
country, he wanted all of them. He decided to make some boats with the planks and screws and
hoped to sail the seas until land. He found a new country with even more bananas and even
more stores to infiltrate so he told the banana buds of his banana buds to take over to their
base.
Seventh, he was a genius AND a hero… But he still wasn’t satisfied with it.He found another
giant landform to invade called the moon or as he says, “A gray earth” but he couldn’t jump high
enough so he decided to build a banana tower to reach to the moon but it unsurprisingly had no
shops.So he terraformed it with fertilizer from the shop and obviously water to make it look
green and planted some seeds from the shop.He now had even more troops in his army of the
bananas.
Eighth, now he was an astronaut AND a genius AND a hero… But he still was not satisfied with
his achievements so he wanted to expand to the solar system so he started with Pluto then
captured Mars after that captured Jupiter and all the other planets. They seemed like
otherworldly creatures but they are just bananas. All of this in only one decade.
Ninth, he was a world conqueror AND an astronaut AND a genius AND a hero… But he still
wasn’t satisfied with all of this so he built a base of operations on all of the planets, the main one
being on the earth. Afterwards he made many farms near each base. Now his banana army
had grown to massive amounts up to millions billions.
Tenth, But he didn’t notice that some apples had come on the banana tower and snuck into the
base. They were planning an attack to gain power. The apples were angry about the news on
the Earth being all about bananas! The humans only stopped eating bananas, not apples! So
they wanted to recover their reputation and respect and make apples the best grub.
<Monday, September 18th>
The betrayal
Chapter 2
When the apples attacked, they were busy and at the most vulnerable spot for their base.
Eleventh, Once they’ve reached their opponents base, the apples had sabotaged the automatic
planting system so instead of planting banana trees, it planted apple trees. All the resources
allocated to growing their army was used for the apple's own greedy needs. Although some
apples protested enough to stop the plan, the damage has already been done and almost all of
their resources drained.
Twelfth, the apples secretly decided to steal resources but instead on a smaller base like the
banana’s base on pluto. The bananas noticed a small drain but never thought anything of it. The
bananas eventually fixed it but didn’t suspect anything.
Thirteenth, the apples still were not happy enough as the bananas were still operating without
any problems so they found out in one of their classified papers, it said that the entire banana
sprinkler system was relying on a software. They took advantage of that by evading into the
system and changing the settings to over water the plants and waste their water.
Fourteenth, the bananas only realized when they ran out of water to use and their water
synthesizer was being overloaded. They swiftly changed the settings as fast as their internet
could handle but they still needed to wait a week to regain the water. The apple's plan had
stunted the growth successfully.
Fifteenth, the bananas needed to prevent any more damage to their banana army from the
apple's ecstatic rampant war. The bananas decided to set a trap in their system by adding
security measures.Now, the trap was set.
Sixteenth, the apples were ready to continue so they built their own base on earth and decided
their next attack would be to remotely hack the system and delete everything.The apples
remotely connected to the system and brute force the password.After a few they saw that the
firewall blocked them after brute forcing ten attempts and got their ip exposed in the banana’s
system logs.
Seventeenth, the bananas soon found out and connected to their system using the system logs
and deleted all of the documents and reports as well as the software they used to connect to
their system and backdoored their system so they can always have access to their system.
Eighteenth, the apples took a great setback as all of their reports of how the bananas system
were wiped off the system and could not be regained as of the new security measures. Weeks
of data was gone.
Nineteenth, the apples took a break for a bit but the banana didn’t.Their army was still growing
and still getting stronger.The apples decided to rebuild their software and the banana definitely
won the ongoing battle or now although it might change… or will it?Time will tell.
Twentieth, during this a orange was In between and wanted to peacefully resolve the war. It
wasn't going to be an easy task as the war has already been ongoing and much destruction has
already been caused which normally and slowly leads to more wars but for now, it shall be the
bananas winning the ongoing war.
The oranges
Chapter 3
Twenty first - The oranges tried thinking of a plan to stop the war so the oranges made a small
hut to think in. One orange built a database to store ideas. One built an open vpn with a
server.And they agreed to not betray each other.
Twenty second, The oranges were thinking hard on how to stop the war and then they thought if
they built a program to hack any computer system, they could stop the apples from hacking the
banana database.Most of the oranges agreed to make the program, the others strengthened the
old ideas.
Twenty third, The idea database grew every day with small, big, rational, and irrational ideas
and maybe even crazy ideas like “Killing one side of the war for it to end”, of course it didn’t get
approved as the oranges main mission was to end the war while causing the least possible
damage or at least less than if the war went on without interruption.There were also more
rational ideas like “giving both side a gift from each other to calm down the war” which got
accepted.Not only that, Some small things like adding firmware to auto update their software
and operating system while night time.And finally some ideas are really big like “Making a whole
new database with fake ideas and making it with low to no security to hide our real idea
database”, these types of ideas normally take a long time to get reviewed as it has a lot of
factors to decide if it’s good or bad.
Twenty fourth, About the big idea mentioned in the previous paragraph, they decided to accept
it and started working on it. They then had their first problem, what would the disguised ideas
be.They weirdly thought of “Teach everyone how to cook zucchini pie with only a pan, a stove,
and the ingredients.”.Most of the oranges agreed that it was good.
Twenty fifth, The oranges thought that since they already had a hacking program, they could
just hack both sides of the war and set up a backdoor just in case they needed access to their
systems quickly.They did it and luckily didn’t get caught.
Twenty sixth, The apples finally decided to finish their break and continued working on finding a
way to circumvent the bananas security measures and find a way to wreak havoc on their
operations.What they didn’t know was that the bananas were not taking a break and improved
their security measures by ten fold.
Twenty seventh, The bananas ran out of good ideas to do so they thought of just polishing their
old ideas to work stronger, better, more efficient, and faster.Most bananas were bored of their
jobs so they switched jobs and got the banana’s operations to work more efficiently and have
better banana moral.
Twenty eighth, The oranges were wrapping most of their ideas up and were quickly doing more
ideas. After time the oranges had better ideas and bigger ideas.They were growing at a rapid
rate but after a while reduced to a crawl.
Twenty nine, The oranges decided to only act when action is required and laid dormant until
something happens. Little did they know that was going to happen very
Soon.
Thirty, The apples decided to launch a sneak attack with their stolen computers from the
bananas. The computer has access to the system although with low access they could find
some major exploit to raise their access level and deleted some files. The oranges saw this and
quickly logged in and kicked them out without a trace.
<Tuesday, October 3th>
The log
Chapter 4
While the oranges were very anonymous, secretive and very careful, one single log was
found by the apples while trying to disconnect without a local Tor server to hide the IP. Thirty
one: This single mistake was crucial as it allowed low level connection protocols to be used by
“anonymous users” and non-administrators. One of these protocols included the ping command;
the apples used a vulnerability in the ping command using the ICMP protocol.
Thirty two: with the ping command, they could forge requests and perform a SSF attack where
the client requests a server to “forge” a request to send to an internal server by injecting code in
the default data ping uses to test connections to a server. Its ability to forge a request means

they could make a “post” and “get” request to add data and receive data from the oranges
server. This level of privilege would allow them to see a hidden webpage on the public internet
nested deep within domain paths.
Thirty three: the straw that broke the camel’s back was that the webpage was vulnerable to a
file inclusion bug from the language settings and a link in the website leading to an upload page
in the same TLD ( Top level domain ). This would mean that they could set a language to an
invalid file that was parsed, resulting in the code in the file being executed. This would mean
that they had remote code execution in their hands, the worst possible vulnerability that a server
could have.
Thirty four: fortunately the database and all the sensitive information was not stored on the web
server . Unfortunately, the servers were connected directly with a network, which meant that the
oranges were compromised. By now the oranges had already been notified by suspicious
activity and shutdown all connections from the server.
Thirty five: the oranges luckily had a backup server in case this happened due to the careful
nature of the oranges. They made some changes to the backup server ( like patching the
vulnerabilities ) and overridden the main servers with the backup servers and resumed
connections with the other main systems. Although the crisis was averted, the apples finding out
meant that the oranges were no longer anonymous and now were more vulnerable than ever
before.
Thirty six: the crisis not only stunted the entire growth of the oranges but also caused a
significant drop in their ideas and data as the reason? The backups happened once every
month to reduce their database load but after the crisis, they changed it to once every other day
which is a pretty substantial increase.
Thirty seven: in the apples system, were now newly sensitive documentation on the banana
topology and how it works. This also included all of the banana servers lP, some of them were
ones that the apples didn’t even discover yet. The apples were now focusing on making more
physical bots to add to their botnet for the sole purpose of running DDOS attacks and running
brute force attacks against the bananas ( and maybe even the oranges )
Thirty eight: luckily even though the apples were aware of the oranges now, the apple didn’t
seem to notice any suspicious signs of backdoors. Even though their server load seemed
higher, more read requests from “OSsysproman.sys.exe”. The internet activity also seemed to
be sending the entire database to an unknown linux server.
Thirty nine: The bananas were minding their business and were rebooting and optimizing their
software and systems. The banana team was so large that it resulted in having their own OS
instead of windows or macOS. Since the server was made for bananas, it was easily
recognizable if it was.
